==Association with witches==
{{main|Pendle witches}}

On [[Good Friday]], 10 April 1612,{{sfnp|Sharpe|2002|p=2|ps=}} Malkin Tower was the venue for perhaps the most well-known alleged witches' coven in English legal history.{{sfnp|Bennett|1993|p=22|ps=}} The house was home to Elizabeth Southerns, also known as Demdike,{{efn|name=Demdike|"Demdike" is derived from "devil woman", suggesting that Elizabeth Southerns was "feared and loathed within the community".{{sfnp|Clayton|2007|p=204|ps=}}}} and her granddaughter Alizon Device,{{sfnp|Froome|2010|p=38|ps=}} two of the alleged Pendle witches.<ref name="Executions"/>

